Something has always existed. According to physics, there can never be true physical nothingness—though there can be times when existence resembles nothing, such as a vacuum (the state of minimum possible energy) (Phys.org). Creating a space where there are no quantum fluctuations requires an enormous amount of energy, and there would be a remnant of that energy in that space afterwards if the fluctuations were flushed out, plus an unstable environment (1veritasium). Even on computers, deleted data is not actually tossed away, by rather written over.

## Lists

Unordered

- Create a list by starting a line with `+`, `-`, or `*`
- Sub-lists are made by indenting 2 spaces:
  - Marker character change forces new list start:
    - Ac tristique libero volutpat at
    * Facilisis in pretium nisl aliquet
    - Nulla volutpat aliquam velit
- Very easy!

Ordered

1. Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet
2. Consectetur adipiscing elit
3. Integer molestie lorem at massa

4. You can use sequential numbers...
5. ...or keep all the numbers as `1.`

Start numbering with offset:

57. foo
1. bar

content:
# Bracchia hunc hoc venisse versat

## Ducunt arcus intus

Lorem markdownum conviva mutare spernit. Ora et numine ruit turis dominam
speciem! Hunc dum locus matrem procumbere ore, potest, fraxineam, mater modo et
unam **essem**, per? Meritis nec Alcathoi pulsare.
![Relax](https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1481833761820-0509d3217039?ixlib=rb-1.2.1&ixid=MnwxMjA3fDB8MHxzZWFyY2h8NHx8cmVsYXh8ZW58MHx8MHx8&auto=format&fit=crop&w=500&q=60)

Mortis errat simillima imis **stuppea** nihil. Auxilio desuetudine suci tendimus
Achivi Delius rector inconsumpta bubo, inferiora *cingo* atricolor! Sitae exitus
tibi: non cognatas aqua canescere mearum vulnere, mota praesepibus nectare
illos, currus ex **sacris nepotum**. Se venit Amorque positus nocte Rex austri
nobis vulnera atque, possis? Devotaque opis anguis *at tumuli Acheloia* specie,
diu quidem: et est, nos.

## Laevae et iterum expalluit gerit

Conlato blandita volucris. Est hoc unde, caelestia lustrat. Tellure summos!

Ferox **fistula partem poposcerat** fides! Hic foret gemitum diu si illi, nec ab
quem defecto; meorum. Tenenti et gravitate offer vestigia exstat ignes non cum
sustinuit dicta. Movebant fuderat, sed ferae nolit quod terraeque locumque deos
fretum blanda.

## Concedite videre carica illa

Laudatae iaculum flavescere liceat ignota. Dant consolante formis orbem: poenas
ore sole Telamonius, secuti quae silvis fuisses; per exemplo glaebis exsecrere.
Tigris exsecratur haec sperne; Coronida aevum maternos imagine.
![relax2](https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1512474331201-782fc6a4ee29?ixlib=rb-1.2.1&ixid=MnwxMjA3fDB8MHxzZWFyY2h8MjV8fHJlbGF4fGVufDB8fDB8fA%3D%3D&auto=format&fit=crop&w=500&q=60)

Duo tum noxae **efficiet Helicona** noviens
[colla](http://www.cadme-qui.com/prima.html): manet sequenti superis tanget
**qui** saucius minoribus vitam natus. Et maxime bella saevit ardet mollit
ferrea umbrosum gnato sonum coniecto patrii precesque ad. Pater vestes. Tu aere
eumque: dea erat gentes intres robur morari. Stridores cubilia abesto, ad in
**quod** spectantur mento mihi esset tenet Adonis iactatibus Troiae quidem
plurimus tibi!

## Sanguineaque longo res vidit Priamoque quae desertaque

Humano coeperunt Eumenides. Et ore vitiasse, ter medullis velit, Oresitrophos
moneo, scelerate. Tellus de Gryneus muris foramina pudoris domus mortisque
parum: ad tenuit pelle cognovi. Habuit antiqua terrarumque hinc **gaudebat
habent** me portus lacu arboris postmodo per, igne. Ait non, ut cortice dextra
quaeritur positu.

1. Theseus nunc convicia communis extentam nulla
2. Ea porrigit carpit
3. Corpus auribus recenti sollemnia lacrimis rogumque
4. Ilex vestigia pro
5. Minimum merentem telluris hic hostes
6. Videntur nunc obliquaque vesci

Suae lacrimisque novo Chione non et portus **flexit hostis amensque**, Diana?
Nil hanc talia [quaesitus](http://www.passa.net/editus), nec Iani petite
hospitis caritura carinis?
